A proficiency in German at the CEF level B1 is a prerequisite for joining this course. You can test yourself online at https://www.goethe.de/de/spr/kup/tsd.html
The following topics will be covered in the course: people, work and leisure, cultural differences, communication, social problems, memories etc. Course materials include written texts and audio files on these topics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Intermediate course that aims to expand students' vocabulary and increase active language use through oral and written exercises.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student is able: 1. to express her/himself orally and in written form and explain her/his viewpoints; 2. to understand more complicated texts and find important information from the texts; 3.  to use more complicated grammatical structures.
